casebody.data:
PETER HAULENBECK, Respondent, v. SPENCER HEACOCK, et al., Impleaded, &c., Appellants.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and Truax, JJ,

Decided April 4, 1881. Appeals by the appellants, severally, from an order enjoining each of them from collecting judgments obtained by them respectively. Armstrong <6 Briggs, for appellants. Whitehead & StacJcpoole, for respondents. Sedgwick, Ch. J.,

wrote for affirmance of order appealed from, as to both appellants, with $10 costs, and disbursements; Freedman and Truax, JJ., concurred.
